    "minides": "Maserati's first in-house mid-engine supercar in decades — built on a carbon-fibre monocoque, powered by the bespoke 630 hp Nettuno twin-turbo V6, with iconic butterfly doors.",
    "description": "The Maserati MC20 is the Italian marque's first bespoke mid-engine supercar since the MC12 of 2004, launched in India in December 2021. It is built around a carbon-fibre monocoque chassis, features iconic upward-swinging butterfly doors, and is powered by Maserati's all-new Nettuno 3.0-litre twin-turbocharged V6 engine producing 630 hp and 730 Nm, paired with an 8-speed dual-clutch transmission driving the rear wheels. The MC20 Coupe is priced at ₹3.45 crore, while the MC20 Cielo — a convertible variant featuring a one-of-a-kind electrochromic glass roof that transitions between transparent and opaque and retracts in 12 seconds — is priced at ₹5.02 crore. Despite being 85 kg heavier than the Coupe, the Cielo still manages a 3.0-second 0-100 sprint. The cabin houses dual 10.25-inch screens, an optional Sonus Faber audio system, and optional ADAS including adaptive cruise control and surround cameras."
  },
